text: Kiryabinskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kiryabinsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 485 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 40 km from Uchaly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Kiryabinskoye
